body.start:
Gigiizhiitaa na ji - maajitaayan izhichigewin gaye ji - ozhitooyan nagamon? Giishpin nitam ezhichigewinan, daanginan Start naazhaya’ii wewiibinaabin gaa-izhichigeyan EarSketch. Giishpin nagajitooyan, daanginan Skip to start coding.

izhinikaade inwewin Python, daanginan naazhaya’ii ji-aanjisidooyan inwewin JavaScript.
body.codeEditor: Aazhawaatebii’ iganing ge - dazhi - ozhitooyan nagamon. Gaa - dazhiikang wabandan ji - naagwak nagamon.
body.runCode: Waabandan owe RUN Daaginan RUN gaa - dazhiikang dananokiiwin ogijaya’ ii gaa - dazhiikang.
body.previewMusic: Endananokiing(E) giga - waabandaan minik gaa - anokiidaman diba’ iganensens. Naazhaya’ ii gidananokiiwin, enitaagwakin nagamonan omaa ayaawan.
body.playMusic: Ogijaya’ ii daanginan(E) da - naagwad ge - onji - waabandaman ji - gidotooyan.Gidaa - daanginaan gaa - ozhaawashko - shaagawaag ji - gidotooyan .
body.exploreCode: Namanjaya’ ii waabanjiganing ge - onji - mikaman.Daanginan daangibii’ igan ogijaya’ ii ji - baakinamang gaye giba’ aman.Baatayiinadoon daangininganan.Baamaa giga - waabandaanan eshtigemagakin.
body.addSounds: Nitam mekaged < span class = "text-yellow-500 text-3xl align-middle icon icon-headphones"> NOONDAAGWAD. Naazhaya’ii ipidoon mekagemagak daanginan biinjibii’iganan ji-noondaman 4,000+ nagamonan, negamowaad gaa-gii-ozhitoowaad.
body.saveCode: Aazha ganawenjigemagak < span class = "text-yellow-500 text-3xl align-middle icon icon-embed2"> MAZINA’IGANAN. Gidaa-waabandaanan mazina’igan e’apii gaa-ozhichigaadegin, gaye inwewin.
body.readCurriculum: Na’ iiwaya’ iing inanokiiwibii’ iganan.Daanginan ji - waabandaman inanokiiwibii’ igan gaye ge - wiiji’ ik daanginan ji - waabandamang.
body.end: Howa! Gigiizhitoon anokiiwin. Mii dash ge - izhi - maajitooyan gidochigewin. Daanginan oshki-anokiiwin gaye gaa-maajii-dazhiikang.

sound.description: Audio file to insert on track, typically this is a constant from the sound browser

makeBeat.description: Ozhising epiitaweg asigibii’ iganan. AMANJI IGO daa - akwaawan asigibii’ iganan .16 eta ji - akwaagin asigibii’ iganan(e.g .16, 32, 64, etc.), mii omaa ge - onji - gikendaman ekobii’ igaadegin asigibii’ iganan(16 akwaawan asigibii’ iganan.)

sound.description: A single sound file or a list/array of sound files, typically this is a constant from the sound browser

start.description: Location within the track to start pattern

beat.description: A string indicating the rhythmic pattern to play. "0" plays the sound file for a sixteenth note. "+" ties (i.e. continues or sustains) the sound file for an additional sixteenth note. "-" rests (i.e. creates silence) for a sixteenth note. If the first argument to makeBeat is a list/array of sounds, the "0" through "9" will play the sound at that list/array index for a sixteenth note.

makeBeatSlice.description: Ozhising epiitaweg asigibii’ iganan giwiindamaagon wenji - maajiseg nagamon. MakeBeat, apane maajitaamagad, makeBeatSlice ji - ozhitooyan bebakaanakin enitaagwakin mii go bezhigon nagamon.

sound.description: A single sound file, typically this is a constant from the sound browser

start.description: Location within the track to start pattern

beat.description: A string indicating the rhythmic pattern to play. "0" through "9" plays the sound file at the location specified at the corresponding index of the beatNumber list/array for a sixteenth note. "+" ties (i.e. continues or sustains) the sound file for an additional sixteenth note. "-" rests (i.e. creates silence) for a sixteenth note.

sliceStarts.description: A list/array of starting locations within audio file. For example, [1.0, 2.5] creates two time locations at measure 1 and measure 2.5 of the sound file that can be referenced in the beat string by "0" and "1" respectively.

parameter.description: Constant indicating which parameter of the effectType to create the envelope for. (See Every Effect Explained in Detail in the curriculum sidebar for a complete list of effect parameters.)

start.description: Location within the track to start pattern

beat.description: A string indicating the rhythmic envelope pattern to create. "0" through "9" uses the effect parameter value at the location specified at the corresponding index of the effectList list/array for a sixteenth note. "+" ties (i.e. continues or sustains) the parameter value for an additional sixteenth note. "-" ramps (i.e. creates a gradual change) to the next parameter value for a sixteenth note.
